22 (3) The Maryland Capitol Police of the Department of General Services
23 may include sworn police officers.
24 (b) A member of the Maryland Capitol Police of the Department of General
25 Services may not be involuntarily transferred from a site to another site.
26 (c) Subject to subsection (d) of this section, a Maryland Capitol Police officer has
27 all the powers granted to a peace officer and a police officer of the State.
